<dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark">
  <label>T1090.001 — Internal proxy / SOCKS chaining</label>
  <description>Internal proxy / SOCKS chaining (T1090.001). See cases/t1090_001_internal_proxy/README.md for the full triage runbook.</description>

  <fieldset submitButton="false" autoRun="true">
    <input type="time" token="time">
      <label>Time range</label>
      <default>
        <earliest>-24h@h</earliest>
        <latest>now</latest>
      </default>
    </input>
    <input type="text" token="src_filter" searchWhenChanged="true">
      <label>Source IP</label>
      <default>*</default>
    </input>
  </fieldset>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Active alerts</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`internal_proxy_chain`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats count</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="colorBy">value</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,1,5]</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x53a051","0xf8be34","0xdc4e41"]</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Distinct sources</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`internal_proxy_chain`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| stats dc(src)</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Alerts</title>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>`internal_proxy_chain`
| where like(src, "$src_filter$") OR "$src_filter$"="*"
| eval window=strftime(_time, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")
| sort -_time</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="count">25</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Underlying activity, top sources</title>
      <chart>
        <search>
          <query>index=zeek sourcetype=zeek:conn 'id.resp_p' IN (1080, 3128, 8080, 8888, 9050)
| timechart span=15m count BY src limit=8</query>
          <earliest>$time.earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$time.latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="charting.chart">column</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.stackMode">stacked</option>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>About this detection</title>
      <html>
        <h3>T1090.001 — Internal proxy / SOCKS chaining</h3>
        <p>Stands up an internal pivot to obfuscate east-west traffic — SOCKS proxy on a compromised host that the operator routes lateral connections through. Defeats simple src→dest IP-pair reasoning.</p>
        <p>Per (1-h window, src) on internal proxy ports {1080, 3128, 8080, 8888, 9050}, count distinct internal destinations. Operators chain through 3+ pivot hosts; benign tools hit at most one.</p>
        <p>
          Tuning + false-positive notes:
          <a href="https://github.com/JacobRHess/detlab/blob/main/cases/t1090_001_internal_proxy/README.md" target="_blank">cases/t1090_001_internal_proxy/README.md</a>
        </p>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
</dashboard>
